text: Yelena Piraynen (born 15 March 1969) is a Belarusian cross-country skier. She competed in four events at the 1994 Winter Olympics. She was the first woman to represent Belarus at the Olympics. ==References== Category:1969 births Category:Living people Category:Belarusian female cross-country skiers Category:Olympic cross-country skiers of Belarus Category:Cross-country skiers at the 1994 Winter Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Minsk
